---
import TerminalWindow from './TerminalWindow.astro';
---

<section class="py-24 sm:py-32 px-5 sm:px-8 section-divide">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <div class="font-mono text-xs text-manager mb-3 sm:text-center tracking-widest reveal">MANAGER SESSIONS</div>
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold sm:text-center mb-4 tracking-[-0.02em] reveal stagger-1">
      One agent manages the rest.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary sm:text-center text-[15px] leading-relaxed max-w-lg sm:mx-auto mb-12 reveal stagger-2">
      A manager session is a Claude Code instance that monitors your other sessions, sends them instructions, and reports status back to you. Define a schedule and goals, and the manager keeps your fleet on track.
    </p>

    <!-- Terminal demo -->
    <div class="reveal stagger-3">
      <TerminalWindow title="manager" class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <div class="space-y-1.5 text-xs sm:text-sm">
          <div><span class="text-manager font-bold">manager:</span> <span class="text-text-secondary">Scheduled check. 3 workers.</span></div>
          <div class="pt-1.5 border-t border-border mt-1.5"></div>
          <div><span class="text-success">auth-refactor</span> <span class="text-text-tertiary">·</span> <span class="text-success">running</span> <span class="text-text-tertiary">· 80% done</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-success">api-tests</span> <span class="text-text-tertiary">·</span> <span class="text-success">running</span> <span class="text-text-tertiary">· 12 passing</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-secondary">frontend-ui</span> <span class="text-text-tertiary">·</span> <span class="text-secondary">stalled 14m</span></div>
          <div class="pt-1.5 border-t border-border mt-1.5"></div>
          <div><span class="text-manager font-bold">manager:</span> <span class="text-text-secondary">Restarted frontend-ui with fix context. Next check in 30m.</span></div>
        </div>
      </TerminalWindow>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
